replies.body:
I understand that, but providing that I follow the rules laid out by "RiotGames" I should not have people verbally attacking me for using a system in place to keep players comfortable and games feeling fair. 

Come to think of it, the very idea that these players "Want to play, what they want." tells me; they should be playing [Blind Normal] and not [Draft Normal]
{{sticker:zombie-brand-facepalm}}

Sorry, not going to read this, I thank you for your input; however late, but we're basically poking a dead horse now... and {{champion:120}} would not approve.

This topic is dead, whether mine or anyone else, it's fallen off the list and has essentially been answered. Not only that, but you're one of those people who approve of toxic hateful behavior, and believe that I deserved the abuse I received.  So, I will not be taking any more of my time to satisfy your comments. 

{{sticker:slayer-jinx-wink}}

To be fair, you're a very aggressive person, and I would like to ask that you refrain from posting in this topic any further. 

Thank you.
{{sticker:sg-lux-2}}

They might not have been kind, however─ there was no malicious intent behind my actions.  

I simply had an option to ban a champion, and I took it.  Had the person picking Irelia been legitimately first pick, I would not have banned─ but considering the high chance of having to face her on the opposing team, I did what I had to; to increase the entire teams odds of winning.  

{{sticker:sg-ahri-2}}

Thank you, no nothing spiteful, unless you count the word "sweetie" used sarcastically as toxic.  
For example, one of my messages was roughly; "Listen Sweetie, I did not ban Irelia just to be hateful..."

{{sticker:slayer-jinx-catface}}
